Hi,

Cigna Healthcare is now defending a patent infringement suit brought by Factor2 Multimedia Systems, LLC in the Eastern District of Texas before Judge Kernodle, a venue known for tight scheduling orders that compress the window for building an invalidity case. Factor2 has the profile of a litigation-focused NPE, and cases like Factor2 Multimedia Systems, LLC v. CIGNA Healthcare in that district tend to move toward claim construction faster than defendants expect.

Stilta works with in-house IP teams on exactly this kind of situation: rapid prior-art searches against the asserted patents, claim-chart analysis, and a concrete assessment of whether IPR petitions at the PTAB are worth pursuing before litigation costs compound.

If it would be useful, we can put together a focused overview of what an early invalidity and IPR viability review would look like for this matter. Happy to set up a brief call at your convenience.

Best regards,
Astrid Atle
